item.description:
TIL about the Intersection Observer API. It allows us to asynchronously observe changes in the intersection of a target element with an ancestor element or with a top-level document&rsquo;s viewport.
Let&rsquo;s see a small example:
// Create the observer and pass it a callback function. // The callback will run whenever a threshold is crossed. var options = { root: document.querySelector(&#39;#scrollArea&#39;), rootMargin: &#39;0px&#39;, threshold: 1.0 } var observer = new IntersectionObserver(callback, options); // Watch this element, please: var target = document.
